# Engineering Rules

- On startup, acquire all github tools and get them ready to run.
- Work in small, reviewable increments.
- Prefer the simplest design that supports the current behavior and leaves clear options for the next step.
- Keep tests close to the behavior being changed.
- Use github.com/unclebob/Acceptance-Pipeline-Specification for Gherkin acceptance tests.
- For Go commands, use a per-worktree `GOCACHE` such as `.gocache` inside that worktree to avoid writing outside the workspace and triggering escalations.
- Run acceptance generation and acceptance tests sequentially.
- Avoid running `go test ./...` concurrently with acceptance generation.
- For headless verification that touches app or acceptance packages, run `./scripts/headless-check.sh` instead of plain `go test ./...`; the plain full-suite command can hang in the default Ebitengine/macOS GUI path.
- Run the relevant local verification command before handoff whenever the project has one.
- Do not edit mutation testing or acceptance mutation manifests by hand; allow approved mutation tools to update those manifests as part of their normal runs.
- Do not commit unrelated local changes or generated artifacts unless required for the task.
- Before relying on an unfamiliar command, inspect local help or project documentation.
